Pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(thinly sliced). Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}(thinly sliced). Trim the @spring onion{1}(thinly sliced). Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(finely chopped), deseed then finely chop. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Sprinkle the @cornflour{10%g} into a #mixing bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and toss to coat thoroughly.

IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium high heat. Line a #plate{} with some #kitchen paper{}. When the pan is hot, add the chicken. Stir-fry until browned all over, ~{8-10%minutes}. Transfer to the lined plate to absorb any excess oil.

> Tip! Cook the pork in batches if necessary to make sure the meat doesn't stew!

Pop your frying pan back on high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{} if the pan is dry. Add the onion and mushrooms to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and stir fry until the mushrooms are browned and the onion softened, ~{6-7%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then pour in the @bulgogi sauce{75%g} and @water{75%ml}(for the sauce). Stir together to combine.

Add the chicken back into the mixture, bring to the boil and simmer until thickened and reduced by a third, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and spoon it into #bowls{}. Divide the bulgogi chicken between the rice and finish with a sprinkling of spring onion and chilli. Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you have chosen diced chicken breast instead of pork, no need to cut the chicken up, just coat the diced chicken breast with the cornflour the same way you would coat the pork.

> Step 4 MOD: If you have opted for chicken breast instead of pork, follow the same instructions above, cook the chicken breast for 8-10 mins instead of 4-5 mins, follow the rest of the step.

> Step 6 MOD: If you've opted for chicken breast instead of pork, follow the same instructions as above. The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.